summary: This is a travel authorization email from the DOJ's E2 travel system, approving a trip for an FBI agent to conduct a witness interview in Beverly Hills, CA as part of the Epstein investigation. The trip is scheduled for February 26-29, 2020.

persons.name: R2ONYS13402
persons.context: The traveler authorized for the trip to conduct a witness interview for the Epstein investigation. The ID format suggests an FBI agent designation.

events.title: Witness Interview Travel Authorization
events.description: Travel authorization approved for an FBI agent to travel to Beverly Hills, CA to conduct a witness interview as part of the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The DOJ was actively conducting witness interviews for the Epstein investigation as of February 2020.
Travel was authorized for an FBI agent (R2ONYS13402) to Beverly Hills, CA from February 26-29, 2020.
The purpose was specifically listed as 'Epstein Investigation - Witness interview'.
The document shows the use of the DOJ's E2 travel authorization system for official investigation travel.
